1. *Opustite* se malo, previše radite. (Relax a bit, you work too much.)
2. Molim vas da *opustite* ruku, veoma me boli. (Please loosen your grip, it hurts me a lot.)
3. Morate *opustiti* svoje zahtjeve ako želite postići kompromis. (You have to lower your demands if you want to reach a compromise.)
4. *Opustio* sam se kada sam vidio da su svi dobro. (I relaxed when I saw that everyone was okay.)
5. Nisam se mogao *opustiti* dok nisam završio sve zadatke. (I couldn't relax until I finished all the tasks.)
6. Nakon napornog dana, dobro je *opustiti* se uz knjigu. (After a hard day, it's good to relax with a book.)
7. *Opustila* se kada je shvatila da je situacija pod kontrolom. (She relaxed when she realized that the situation was under control.)
8. Nemojte se *opuštati* previše, još ima puno posla. (Don't relax too much, there's still a lot of work to do.)
9. Ljekar joj je rekao da se *opusti* i da pokuša da smanji stres. (The doctor told her to relax and try to reduce stress.)
10. Morate *opustiti* mišiće prije nego što počnete sa vježbanjem. (You have to loosen your muscles before you start exercising.)

Note: In Serbian, the word "opustite" can have multiple forms depending on the context and grammatical rules, such as "opusti" (imperative singular), "opušten" (adjective), "opuštajući" (present participle), etc.